# Security headers for the deployed dashboard (Netlify / Cloudflare Pages
# `_headers` format — Vite copies this file from public/ to the dist root). If you
# deploy behind nginx/Caddy/other, translate these into that layer's header
# config. These apply to the BUILT site only, never the Vite dev server, so HMR is
# unaffected.
#
# The CSP is the main mitigation for the localStorage-token XSS exposure (see
# src/lib/auth-tokens.ts): `connect-src 'self'` stops a script from exfiltrating
# tokens to a third-party origin, and `script-src 'self'` blocks injected/inline
# scripts. If the API is served from a SEPARATE origin in production (not the same
# origin via a proxy), add that origin to `connect-src`.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; img-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; form-action 'self'
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), camera=(), microphone=(), payment=()
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
